title.narrative: 6.1 IMPROVED POLICY ENVIRONMENT & SYSTEMS FOR DISADVANTAGED & EXCLUDED CHILDREN

description.narrative: Evidence is used for policy development and monitoring progress towards the child-relevant Sustainable Development Goals., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Climate Change, Disaster Risks And Envionmental Degradation, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Evaluation, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Reducing Child Poverty, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved policy environment and systems for disadvantaged and excluded children, guided by data and knowledge.

description.narrative: In collaboration with national and international partners, UNICEF continued to prioritize generation of updated evidence and analysis on situation of children with focus on socio-economic and vulnerability analysis, national social protection issues, social spending, as well as monitoring and evaluation of UNICEF flagship social protection programmes. This has enabled UNICEF toposition itself as a key player influencing sector policy dialogue and regularly introduceprogrammatic enhancements and synergies across different social protection interventions both at national level, and internally. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/01/2022
